column5: I understand completely. I know I can't go while my parents are still alive.... but I just know in my gut that suicide is inevitable. I wish I could offer help or words of wisdom, other than stay strong for as long as you can and keep hoping we are both proven wrong.
I started experiencing restless legs these last few months after being on Lexapro (and Wellbutrin) for a little over a year now. I recently started taking magnesium supplements and they seem to help.
